## Critical Rules

### Layers

```css
/* ALWAYS declare layer order first! */
@layer base, components, utilities, theme-overrides;

/* Layers win by ORDER, not specificity */
/* theme-overrides > utilities > components > base */
```

### @apply Usage

**✅ USE @apply for:**
- Components that repeat 3+ times: `.btn`, `.card`, `.avatar`, `.badge`, `.modal`
- Complex components with states (hover, focus, active)

**❌ DON'T use @apply for:**
- Simple utilities: `.flex`, `.grid`, `.gap-2`, `.mt-4`
- One-off layouts
- Code that appears 1-2 times only

**Rule of thumb:** If it repeats 3+ times → @apply. Otherwise → inline Tailwind.

### Inheritance with @utility

**Component Inheritance:** Define reusable utilities in `components.css`:

```css
/* components.css */
@layer utilities {
  @utility card-base {
    @apply bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 
           flex flex-col items-center gap-4
           transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out shadow-md;
  }
  
  @utility btn-icon {
    @apply w-10 h-10 p-0 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg
           flex items-center justify-center bg-slate-50;
  }
}
```

**Use in components with inheritance on separate line:**

```svelte
<style>
  @reference "tailwindcss";
  
  .list-card {
    @apply card-base;  /* ירושה - שורה נפרדת! */
    @apply border-2 p-5 gap-3 duration-200;
  }
  
  .user-actions {
    @apply btn-icon;  /* ירושה */
    @apply flex gap-3 mt-2;  /* Tailwind */
  }
</style>
```

**Critical Rule:** Custom utilities must be applied on a separate line to distinguish them from built-in Tailwind utilities.

**Critical:** Always add `@reference "tailwindcss";` when using @apply in `<style>` blocks!

### Property Organization

**Critical:** CSS properties MUST be organized in this order:

1. **Positioning** → `position`, `top`, `right`, `z-index`, `display`, `flex`, `grid`
2. **Box Model** → `width`, `height`, `padding`, `margin`, `border`
3. **Typography** → `font-*`, `text-*`, `line-height`, `letter-spacing`
4. **Visual** → `color`, `background`, `opacity`
5. **Effects** → `transform`, `transition`, `animation`, `cursor`

**Workflow:**
- **Development Phase:** Focus on functionality, don't worry about order
- **Organization Pass:** After completing a feature, run a dedicated "CSS organization pass" to reorder properties

**Example:**

```css
.my-component {
  /* Positioning */
  position: relative;
  @apply flex items-center justify-center;
  
  /* Box Model */
  @apply w-full h-20 p-4;
  border: 2px solid;
  @apply border-slate-200 rounded-lg;
  
  /* Typography */
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  
  /* Visual */
  @apply bg-white;
  color: var(--text-main);
  
  /* Effects */
  cursor: pointer;
  @apply transition-all;
}
```

### Nesting

**✅ USE nested CSS for:**
- Theme overrides (all overrides in one block)
- Pseudo-selectors with `&` (`:hover`, `:active`, `:focus`)
- Max 3 levels deep

**❌ DON'T nest:**
- More than 3 levels
- Outside `@layer theme-overrides`

